    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Pride Over a Virus?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Felicia Morales letter says that as a Filipino she is not proud of 'I Love You' computer virus spawned in her country</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''National Pride Over a Virus in Philippines'' (Business Day, May 12): I am a Filipino and I am not proud of the ''I Love You'' virus and the havoc it caused all over the world. I have always been proud of Filipinos' high literacy rate as well as our strong work ethic. But the creation of this virus is clearly not a shining example of intellect and effort put to good use.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''National Pride Over a Virus in Philippines'' (Business Day, May 12): I am a Filipino and I am not proud of the ''I Love You'' virus and the havoc it caused all over the world. I have always been proud of Filipinos' high literacy rate as well as our strong work ethic. But the creation of this virus is clearly not a shining example of intellect and effort put to good use.</p>
        <p>Taking pride in destructive efforts is not in line with what Filipinos should be working toward: an improved national economy and less poverty.</p>
        <p>FELICIA MORALES  New York, May 12, 2000</p>
      </block>
